 Studies I and II'' (Southampton: Harrley Institute, 2007); 207pp, 203pp; essays by scholars\n* Chamberlain, Muriel Evelyn. ''British foreign policy in the age of Palmerston'' ( Longman, 1980).\n* {{cite journal|last=Fenton|first= Laurence|title=Origins of Animosity: Lord Palmerston and The Times, 1830\u201341|journal=Media History|date=2010|volume=16#4 |pages=365\u2013378|doi= 10.1080/13688804.2010.507473}}\n** {{cite book|last=Fenton|first= Laurence|title=Palmerston and The Times: Foreign Policy, the Press and Public Opinion in Mid-Victorian Britain|publisher=IB Tauris|year= 2013|ref=harv}} [https://www.amazon.com/Palmerston-Times-Foreign-Mid-Victorian-Victorian/dp/1780760744/  excerpt]\n* {{cite book|last=Fuller|first=Howard J.|title=Technology and the Mid-Victorian Royal Navy Ironclad: Royal Navy Crisis in the Age of Palmerston|publisher=Routledge|year= 2014|ref=harv}} [https://www.amazon.com/Empire-Technology-Seapower-Palmerston-History/dp/0415370043/ Excerpt]\n* Henderson, Gavin B. \"The Foreign Policy of Lord Palmerston\" ''History'' 22#88 (1938), pp. 335-344, [https://www.jstor.org/stable/24401363 online]\n* {{cite book|last=Hicks|first= Geoffrey|title=Peace, War and party politics: the Conservatives and Europe, 1846\u201359|publisher=Manchester University Press|year=2007|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last=Hoppen|first= K. Theodore|title=The Mid-Victorian Generation, 1846\u20131886|year=1998|ref=harv}}, wide-ranging scholarly survey\n* Leonard, Dick ''Nineteenth Century British Premieres: Pitt to Roseberry'' (2008) pp 245\u201365.\n* Macknight, Thomas. ''Thirty Years of Foreign Policy, a History of the Secretaryships of the Earl of Aberdeen and Viscount Palmerston'' (1855),  [https://archive.org/details/thirtyyearsoffor00mackrich/page/n6 Online free]\n* {{cite book|last=Martin|first= Kingsley|title=The Triumph of Lord Palmerston: a study of public opinion in England before the Crimean War|url=https://archive.org/details/triumphoflordpal0000mart|url-access=regist